![Aerial view of Kibera slum in Nairobi, Kenya. Photo
](https://globalvoicesonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Kibera.jpg)

Aerial view of Kibera slum in Nairobi, Kenya. Photo released under Creative
Commons by the owner Schreibkraft.

Inspired by the [well known](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Humans_of_New_York)
[Humans of New York](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Humans_of_New_York)
photography blog, [Humans of Kibera](http://humansofkibera.tumblr.com/) is [a
project](http://humansofkibera.tumblr.com/aboutus) by Kibera News Network
(KNN), a group of young citizen video news journalists from Kibera in Nairobi,
Kenya. The project documents the lives of the residents of
[Kibera](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kibera)—the largest urban slum in
Africa—on[ a Tumblr blog](http://humansofkibera.tumblr.com/).

